{%- comment -%}
  Vertex AI Recommendations — v2 production slot renderer.
  Replaces the old placeholder snippet (which leaked preview chrome to live).

  ── Placement routing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Pass `placement:` to select the data source and layout class:

  | placement                | data source                                         |
  |--------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
  | pdp_below_atc            | product.metafields.vertex.recs                      |
  | pdp_below_description    | product.metafields.vertex.similar                   |
  | cart_above_checkout      | cart.items[0].vertex.cart_recs → .recs fallback     |
  | home_below_hero          | customer.vertex.recommended_for_you → shop.trending |
  | cart_drawer_below_items  | cart.items[0].vertex.recs (v1 fallback)             |

  ── Arguments ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    placement  {String}   — slot identifier (required; defaults to 'unknown')
    product    {Product}  — anchor product (PDP placements)
    cart       {Cart}     — cart object (cart placements)
    customer   {Customer} — customer object (home RFY logged-in path)
    title      {String}   — section heading (required for customer-facing copy)
    subtitle   {String}   — section subheading (optional)
    rationale  {String}   — dev note shown in theme editor only (never on live)

  ── Safety gates ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  · Empty-state: if rec_products resolves to 0 items, the entire <section>
    is suppressed — no "No products" message renders on live.
  · Preview chrome (VERTEX badge + placement label) only renders when
    request.design_mode is true (theme editor). Never on preview-themed
    shop URLs or live.

  ── Performance ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  · Zero new JS — CSS scroll-snap only.
  · Images: WebP <picture> + JPEG fallback, explicit width/height, lazy.
  · CSS: assets/vertex-recommendations.css (long-cached, ~8 KB).

  Phase 1b-γ.8 (2026-05-02): PR-1 universal foundation.
  See task-1-recommendations.md for PR sequencing + open questions.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign placement    = placement | default: 'unknown'
  assign rec_title    = title     | default: 'You might also like'
  assign rec_subtitle = subtitle  | default: ''

  assign rec_products = ''
  assign rec_source   = 'placeholder'

  case placement
    when 'pdp_below_atc'
      if product and product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif

    when 'pdp_below_description'
      if product and product.metafields.vertex.similar
        assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.similar.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif

    when 'cart_above_checkout'
      if cart and cart.items.first
        if cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.cart_recs
          assign rec_products = cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.cart_recs.value
          assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
        elsif cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs
          assign rec_products = cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
          assign rec_source   = 'metafield_fallback'
        endif
      endif

    when 'home_below_hero'
      if customer and customer.metafields.vertex.recommended_for_you
        assign rec_products = customer.metafields.vertex.recommended_for_you.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      elsif shop.metafields.vertex.trending
        assign rec_products = shop.metafields.vertex.trending.value
        assign rec_source   = 'trending'
      endif

    when 'cart_drawer_below_items'
      if cart and cart.items.first and cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif

    else
      if product and product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif
  endcase

  comment
    Fallback to sample products so the slot is visually populated in the
    preview/development theme before the precompute model goes ACTIVE.
    On live with an ACTIVE model, the metafield branch above always fires
    and this block is skipped.
  endcomment
  unless rec_products
    for col in collections
      if col.products.size >= 4
        assign rec_products = col.products | sample: 4
        break
      endif
    endfor
  endunless

  assign card_count = rec_products.size | default: 0
-%}

{%- comment -%} Empty-state gate: suppress the entire section if no products. {%- endcomment -%}
{%- if card_count == 0 -%}{%- else -%}

<section
  class="vrec-slot vrec-slot--{{ placement }}"
  data-vertex-placement="{{ placement }}"
  data-vertex-anchor="{% if product %}{{ product.id }}{% endif %}"
  data-vertex-product-id="{% if product %}{{ product.id }}{% endif %}"
  data-vertex-source="{{ rec_source }}"
  aria-labelledby="vrec-title-{{ placement }}"
>
  {%- comment -%}
    Preview chrome: VERTEX badge + placement label + rationale tooltip.
    request.design_mode is true ONLY inside the Shopify theme editor.
    It is NOT true on preview-themed shop URLs viewed by non-admins.
    See open question 4 in task-1-recommendations.md before merging to live.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if request.design_mode -%}
    <div class="vrec-slot__preview-chrome">
      <span class="vertex-rec-slot__badge">VERTEX</span>
      <span class="vertex-rec-slot__placement-label">{{ placement | replace: '_', ' ' }}</span>
      {%- if rationale and rationale != '' -%}
        <span class="vertex-rec-slot__why" title="{{ rationale | escape }}">ⓘ why?</span>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>
  {%- endif -%}

  <header class="vrec-slot__header">
    <h2 id="vrec-title-{{ placement }}" class="vrec-slot__title">{{ rec_title }}</h2>
    {%- if rec_subtitle != '' -%}
      <p class="vrec-slot__subtitle">{{ rec_subtitle }}</p>
    {%- endif -%}
  </header>

  <div class="vrec-slot__rail" role="list">
    {%- for rp in rec_products limit: 8 -%}
      {%- render 'vertex-rec-card', product: rp, placement: placement -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
  </div>
</section>

{%- endif -%}
